# ── Go build artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bundles are run with `go run <name>.go`, which compiles to a temp dir — it
# leaves NOTHING in the module. A binary only appears if you manually run
# `go build name.go`, which writes an extensionless file named after the stem.
# Rule: always use `go run`; if you must build, redirect:  go build -o /tmp/x name.go
*.exe
*.test

# ── Coverage / profiling output (Phase 7 pprof + testing) ───────────────────
*.out
*.prof
*.pprof
coverage.out
coverage.html
trace.out

# ── Go workspace files (per-developer) ──────────────────────────────────────
go.work
go.work.sum

# ── Vendor dir (we stay dependency-light) ───────────────────────────────────
vendor/

# ── Editor / OS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ── Local env / secrets (NEVER commit) ──────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.local
